# Testing Guide

All MFEs must maintain 80% coverage on business logic.

## Contract Test (required)

Every MFE must ship a test validating the mount export:

```typescript
import { describe, expect, it, vi } from 'vitest';
import { MFEMountFnSchema } from '@dxp/federation-contracts';
import mount from './mount.js';

describe('mount contract', () => {
  it('satisfies MFEMountFnSchema', () => {
    const result = MFEMountFnSchema.safeParse(mount);
    expect(result.success).toBe(true);
  });
});
```

## Unit Tests

- Use `@testing-library/user-event` — not `fireEvent`
- Mock network with `vi.mock`
- Use `test-utils/mockProps.ts` for `MFEProps`
- Colocate tests: `Button.tsx` → `Button.test.tsx`

## Coverage Exclusions

- `src/index.ts`, `src/bootstrap.tsx`, `src/mount.tsx`
- `src/test-utils/**`
- `src/components/**` (covered by Storybook)
